9 Section 1. R.S. 15:1109.21 and 1109.22(A) are hereby amended and reenacted to
10 read as follows:
11 §1109.21. Renaissance district; creation; jurisdiction
12 A renaissance district is hereby created in any the parish of Rapides having
13 a population of more than one hundred twenty-nine thousand and less than one
14 hundred thirty-two thousand persons according to the most recent federal decennial
15 census, which shall be a political subdivision of the state.
16 §1109.22. Board of commissioners; appointment; terms
17 A. The renaissance district shall be governed by a commission which shall
18 control, administer, and manage its affairs. The commission shall be composed of
19 seven nine commissioners, and each shall be a qualified elector of and domiciled in
20 the parish. Each commissioner shall be appointed for a term of four years as follows:
21 (1) Five Four members shall be appointed by the parish of Rapides
22 governing authority as follows:
23 (a) Two One members member shall be appointed from an existing the
24 prior nonprofit entity renaissance board of directors as long as at least one
25 member of that board exists is capable of serving, after which time two one
26 members member shall be appointed from the residents of the parish who are not
27 employed by the parish police jury and who have experience with juveniles in
